Data Structure:
We use ArrayList to store the list of Category in the Background,
list of Product in the Background,
list of Invoice associating with individual Shopper,
list of Product associating with individual Shopper's shopping cart
list of Product in ProductManager,
list of Category in CatagoryManager,
list of Invoice in InvoiceManager,
list of Background in BackgroundManager,
list of Product in Invoice,
list of Administrator in AdministratorManager,
list of Shopper in ShopperManager.



We use a binary file to store the data.
We serialize all the classes so they can be written to and read from the binary file.
